# ChainSentinel 
### On-Chain Fraud Detection Tool

A blockchain forensics tool that analyzes Ethereum wallet behavior and identifies suspicious fund movement patterns. Built as a group project using real on-chain data.

---

## What it does

Enter any Ethereum wallet address and ChainSentinel will:

1. Check if the wallet is blacklisted — cross-references against Tornado Cash contracts, OFAC sanctions list, and known hacker wallets from rekt.news
2. Detect burst dispersion — flags wallets that send funds to 5+ different wallets within one hour (classic post-hack pattern)
3. Check wallet age — flags wallets that are less than 7 days old but already moving large amounts
4. Visualize the money trail — draws a directed graph showing every wallet and transaction connected to the address

---

## Case Study

We ran this tool on the Drift Protocol exploiter — the wallet responsible for the largest DeFi hack of 2026.

- $285 million stolen in 128 seconds on April 1st 2026
- Carried out by North Korean state hackers (Lazarus Group)
- Entire operation funded with just 10 ETH from Tornado Cash
- Attacker address: `0xD3FEEd5DA83D8e8c449d6CB96ff1eb06ED1cF6C7`

Our tool instantly flagged the address as blacklisted and visualized 28 connected wallets and 27 transactions showing the consolidation of stolen funds.

---

## File Structure

```
chain-sentinel/
├── blacklist.py          # Benedicta — Tornado Cash + hacker wallet reference lists
├── fetch_transcation.py  # OM        — Etherscan API wrapper, pulls transaction data
├── clean_data.py         # Tan       — normalizes and cleans raw transaction data
├── check_burst.py        # Aaliyah   — burst dispersion detection
├── wallet_age_check.py   # OM        — checks how old a wallet is
├── build_graph.py        # Aaliyah   — builds and visualizes the transaction graph
├── analyze_wallet.py     # Team      — combines all checks into one analysis
├── test.py               # Aaliyah   — Phase 1 test script
├── requirements.txt      # all dependencies
├── .env.example          # template for API key setup
└── README.md
```

---

## Setup

1. Clone the repo
```
git clone https://github.com/q8p54rn9jd-creator/chain-sentinel.git
cd chain-sentinel
```

2. Create and activate virtual environment
```
python -m venv .venv
.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
```

3. Install dependencies
```
pip install requests pandas networkx matplotlib python-dotenv
```

4. Add your API key

Create a `.env` file in the root folder:
```
ETHERSCAN_API_KEY=YourKeyHere
```
Get a free key at: https://etherscan.io/apis

---

## How to run

Run the full analysis on any wallet:
```
python analyze_wallet.py
```

Test Phase 1 (fetch + blacklist check):
```
python test.py
```

Check burst dispersion only:
```
python check_burst.py
```

Build the transaction graph:
```
python build_graph.py
```

